text.tspan: Accordion
the visual space in the Toolbox is limited.
To solve this, several components are grouped. If there are mutliple groups
like this, only one can be visible at a given time.
If you expand a new group, the old one gets compressed, thus saving space.
This may seem a little bit annoying at first, but
* it saves scrolling around
* organizes complicated Contents and
* keeps you focussed on your task
In Dashboard
Here you see the Dashboard - this is alway the first frame
in the Toolbox - listing all supported Content Types you
can use on your Pages. So you see the pink "Contents"?
Disappeared
The "Contents" list gets compressed until only
its head is visible.
Frequent Flyer
You will find the Accordion in several places in the Toolbox. It should help you to
devide the Contents of the Toolbox in several sections.
Accordion Head
Hover over the next Accordion Item "CMS" and click it.
Expanded
The "CMS" list gets expanded and marked as active (pink)
